<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-24T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-24T23:00:00-05:00" n="173" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation (3)/100: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-24T23:00:00-05:00">December 24, 1941—11
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>330. Your 276, December 23, noon. This Government has informed the
                            Dominican Government that it perceives no objection to the introduction
                            by the Dominican Government on its own responsibility of a resolution
                            calling for a declaration of war on the part of all the American
                            Republics.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>